The paper discusses the application of decentralized reputation systems in Mobile Ad-Hoc Networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also uses a stochastic process model, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of liars on the reputation system, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
